# Final Corrections — Testing & Verification

## Required testing expectations
- Add positive runtime proof where a previously claimed limitation is no longer real
- Remove parity-only claims when runtime is now supported
- Keep canonical scenario coverage green
- Update stage-specific tests where named-event/runtime semantics changed
- Add regression tests for unsupported/fail-fast behavior where appropriate

## Required verification
Run after each logical correction cycle:
- `npm install`
- `npx tsc -p libs/sdk-dsl/tsconfig.lib.json --noEmit`
- `npx tsc -p libs/sdk-dsl/tsconfig.spec.json --noEmit`
- `npx eslint libs/sdk-dsl`
- `npx vitest run --config libs/sdk-dsl/vite.config.ts`
- `npx vite build --config libs/sdk-dsl/vite.config.ts`

## Commit discipline
After each completed correction cycle:
- commit with a conventional commit message
- keep subject <= 72 chars
- keep commits focused and reviewable

## Final review
Before stopping:
- critically review your own changes
- fix issues you find
- ensure docs and deviations match the real implementation
